Package edu.uky.cs.nil.sabre.io

Interface ObjectPrinter<T>

Type Parameters:
T - the type of the object this object printer can accept
Functional Interface:
This is a functional interface and can therefore be used as the assignment target for a lambda expression or method reference.
@FunctionalInterface public interface ObjectPrinter<T>
An object printer defines how an object should be converted to text. Object printers are associated with Java classes via a printer.
Author:
Stephen G. Ware

  • Method Details

    • print

      void print(Printer printer, T object, Writer output) throws IOException
      Converts an object into text and writes that text to a writer. The printer that called this method is also provided as an argument so that it can be used to print any other objects referenced by the object bring printed.
      Parameters:
      printer - the printer which called this method
      object - the object to be converted to text
      output - the writer to which the text will be written
      Throws:
      IOException - if an exception occurs when writing text to the writer
